  <summary date="2021-01-29T16:19:28Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Stop Blocking Hospitals Act

This bill establishes a new criminal offense for preventing ambulances and vehicles used by fire departments and law enforcement agencies from responding to a call or transporting an individual to a hospital.

An individual who engages in this conduct is subject to criminal penalties&#8212;a fine, a prison term of up to five years, or both.</summary>
